Sentencas: The current energy assets based on fossil fuel are being used extensively.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Thus, the high utilization of these sources has created an alarming situation for scientists and researchers to investigate alternative energy conversion sources followed by devices.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Fuel cell technology is an emerging field of research due to high efficiency and environmentally friendly energy conversion.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The solid oxide fuel cell is a promising candidate as an alternative energy conversion technology.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: In this context, graphene incorporated composite anode materials have been synthesized by solid state reaction with anode composition Al0.1Ni0.2Zn0.7 oxides, and different amounts of 1 wt.%, 1.3 wt.%, and 1.5 wt.% graphene are then incorporated in the prepared composite material.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The crystal structure and surface morphology have been analyzed by X-ray diffraction (XRD) and scanning electron microscopy (SEM).
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The crystallite sizes evaluated by XRD are found in the range of 42-56 nm followed by confirming with SEM images by line drawing.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity has been measured at the function of temperature from 300 degrees C to 650 degrees C by a direct current (DC) four-probe method and maximum value is found to be 0.53 Scm(-1) at 370 degrees C with 1.3% graphene incorporation.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The maximum power density has been achieved of 375 mWcm(-2) at 600 degrees C with 1.3% graphene incorporation.
Titulo: Graphene Incorporated Nanocomposite Anode for Low Temperature SOFCs
